    "summary": "\ud83d\udee1 Founder of the PROMISE Framework | Strategy and Leadership Advisor | M&A | Board Member | Author\n\nDo you have the right culture capabilities in M&A? Take the test:\nhttps://culturema.scoreapp.com/\n\nHow robust is your M&A Integration Design Process? Take the test:\nhttps://maintegrationplan.scoreapp.com/\n\nPROMISE Framework: Creating High-Performance Cultures in Organizations. \nPROMISE is a comprehensive model designed to cultivate high-performance cultures within organizations. This unique approach addresses the key factors that define an organization's culture and unlocks the full potential of a company's most valuable resource \u2013 its people. The acronym PROMISE encompasses People and Professional Development, Rewards, Recognition, and Consequence Management, Organizational Hierarchy and Leadership Styles, Management System, Innovation and Critical Thinking, Strategic Future, and Employee Experience. The PROMISE Framework sets itself apart through its comprehensiveness, simplicity, flexibility, and employee-centric focus. By targeting organizational constraints and removing barriers, the PROMISE Framework paves the way for the development of high-performing organizations.\n\nCEO of Fifth Chrome, a Global Business Strategy and Training company specializing in M&A Integration and Business Transformations, and the Founder of Roundtableinsights, a corporate events company\n\nWorked extensively in 70+ countries across Europe, APAC, South Asia, Middle-East & Africa, and the US with some of the world\u2019s largest companies including General Electric, Stryker, AkzoNobel, Coca-Cola, ABB Kuhne+Nagel, TMF Group, Unit4 and ManpowerGroup. \n\nStrong track record of leading, mentoring, and advising senior business leaders with growth, mergers & acquisitions (M&A), shared services, and transformation initiatives. He has mentored and trained 300+ professionals across the globe. \n\nPassionate about topics related to challenges faced by senior management and regularly speak at and chair various conferences across Asia, Middle East, and Europe. \n\nPublished books:\n- Research Report on Change Management in M&A (https://www.amazon.com/dp/B0B57G4G7F)\n- Right-Fit Digital Strategy to Accelerate Growth (https://www.amazon.com/dp/B08BKQ13TV)\n- 100+ Digital Ideas in 100 Minutes (https://www.amazon.com/dp/B08FBP41WK) \n\nMy LinkedIn Newsletter: https://www.linkedin.com/newsletters/insights-from-m-a-integration-6888927191535550465/",
